ba8fd3cd-1d9f-5ba6-bf19-8cd1e6f1543c,tg:rubgr:277,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"[onleesbaar] 2, Mascarre [?] in imperial collection might well be independent compositions as Mascarade of Ourson & Valentin, (Bast. 215) dated 1566 which differs from the scene in Carnival & Lent; & Mopsus & Nisa (Bast. 216 & 217) dated 1570 also differing from the scene in Carnival & Lent and which may well be reduced compositions by B. himself or after him; 216 is different from Bruegel's own drawing 217.",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

column4: <content>[onleesbaar] 2, Mascarre [?] in imperial collection might well be independent compositions as Mascarade of Ourson & Valentin, (Bast. 215) dated 1566 which differs from the scene in Carnival & Lent; & Mopsus & Nisa (Bast. 216 & 217) dated 1570 also differing from the scene in Carnival & Lent and which may well be reduced compositions by B. himself or after him; 216 is different from Bruegel's own drawing 217.</content>
